  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Gas Station\n\nReturn the starting station index that can complete the circuit, or `-1`.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: gas = [1,2,3,4,5], cost = [3,4,5,1,2]\nOutput: 3\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: gas = [2,3,4], cost = [3,4,3]\nOutput: -1\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: gas = [5], cost = [4]\nOutput: 0\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Track the local choice that leaves the most room for future choices, or sort intervals so conflicts can be resolved with one pass.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def canCompleteCircuit(self, gas, cost):\n        total = tank = start = 0\n        for i, (g, c) in enumerate(zip(gas, cost)):\n            diff = g - c; total += diff; tank += diff\n            if tank < 0: start = i + 1; tank = 0\n        return start if total >= 0 else -1\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Sort first when relative order drives the decision.",
    "Keep the smallest state that proves future feasibility."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def canCompleteCircuit(self, gas, cost):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
    "class_name": "Solution",
    "method_name": "canCompleteCircuit"
  },
